                  <list>
                    <item>
                      <p>Vellum, about 12 1/4 in. by 9 1/2, consisting of 136 leaves, a few of which
                        are slightly stained and torn, especially foll. 1, 9, 110, 111, and 136. The
                        quires, signed with letters from ܐ to ܣ, were originally 15 in number; but
                        the first is now lost. Each page is divided into two columns, of from 33 to
                        37 lines. This volume is written by two hands (foll. 1—43 a and foll. 43
                        a—136) in a fine, elegant Estrangela of the vith cent.</p>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </condition>
